What lifts Bacon's discussions upon force to a higher level than that of barren dialectical debate is, that they were animated by constant reference to a living and growing science due to the later Greeks, and still more to the Arabiane, the science of Optic, including the study of theorgans of vision and perception no less than that of the force acting on them.
